# Sales Analytics Dashboard – Power BI Project

This project showcases an end-to-end Sales Analytics Dashboard built using Power BI. 
It includes insights on store performance, category trends, fiscal month variance, 
and geographic sales distribution.

The dashboard helps business stakeholders monitor key sales metrics, identify 
high-performing areas, and track YoY (Year-over-Year) growth.

---

##  Key Insights & Features

###  Overview Page
- Total Sales: $22M
- YoY comparison & variance
- Sales by Chain (Fashions Direct vs Lindseys)
- New Stores added this year
- Geographic distribution of store sales (map)

###  District Monthly Sales Page
- Monthly sales trend: Last Year vs This Year
- Total Sales Variance % by Fiscal Month
- Top stores by chain and name
- Category-level analysis: Avg $/Unit, variance, and performance clusters

###  New Stores Page
- Performance of newly opened stores
- YoY variance for new stores
- Table showcasing chain → district → store breakdown
- Visuals showing increases and decreases over time

###  Units Sold by Store
- Top stores ranked by total units sold
- Quick way to identify high-volume contributors

